.TH "sysfs_link_change_owner" 9 "sysfs_link_change_owner" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sysfs_link_change_owner \- change owner of a sysfs file.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" sysfs_link_change_owner
.BI "(struct kobject *kobj "  ","
.BI "struct kobject *targ "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ","
.BI "kuid_t kuid "  ","
.BI "kgid_t kgid "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "kobj" 12
object of the kernfs_node the symlink is located in.
.IP "targ" 12
object of the kernfs_node the symlink points to.
.IP "name" 12
name of the link.
.IP "kuid" 12
new owner's kuid
.IP "kgid" 12
new owner's kgid
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function looks up the sysfs symlink entry \fIname\fP under \fIkobj\fP and changes
the ownership to \fIkuid\fP/\fIkgid\fP. The symlink is looked up in the namespace of
\fItarg\fP.

Returns 0 on success or error code on failure.
